Travelex May Sell 600 Million-Pound Payments Unit, Times Says

-- B y   C a r o l i n e   A l e x a n d e r   a n d   C a t h e r i n e   A i r l i e
-- 
2011-04-03T14:33:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-03/travelex-in-talks-to-sell-600-million-pound-unit-times-says.html
Travelex Holdings Ltd. is in talks
with banks on the sale of its global business-payments unit,
which could be worth 600 million pounds ($966.7 million), the
 Sunday Times  of  London  reported, without saying where it got the
information.  The unit handled transactions worth 30 billion pounds last
year, the newspaper reported. Peter Hewer, a London-based
spokesman for Travelex declined to comment when contacted by
telephone.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Caroline Alexander in London at 
 calexander1@bloomberg.net  or
Catherine Airlie at 
 cairlie@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
